onally held truths may be more harmful than reasoned errors.\n\n- Thomas Henry Huxley, Collected Essays of Thomas Henry Huxley\n|\nAny situation, circumstance or challenge is just a distraction and as you remain true to your goals and trust in God they will fall away'.\n\n- Michele Woolley, God's Favor - Breath Of Heaven\n|\nAll changes are positive, just look in the bright side, always and you find the pearl that lies beneath in the sand and a sunny way is there ahead for you!:)\n\n- Ana Claudia Antunes, A-Z of Happiness: Tips for Living and Breaking Through the Chain that Separates You from Getting That Dream Job\n|\nWe all live in suspense, from day to day, from hour to hour; in other words, we are the hero of our own story.\n\n- Mary\n|\nLife is short, death is forever.\n\n- Marsha Qualey, Just Like That\n|\nFailing sucks. But it's better than the alternative.''Which is?''Not even trying.' Now he did look at me, straight on. 'Life's short, you know?\n\n- Sarah Dessen, Along for the Ride\n|\nTo create emptiness in your heart, let it go with love and fill it with infinite love.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nReligiosity developed because successful religions made groups more efficient at turning resources into offspring.' (including art, cathedrals, cities, earthworks, etc?)\n\n- Jonathan\n|\n‎'Based on a true story'? No, thanks. I prefer 'based on a true imagination'.\n\n- Enkelejd\n|\nFor me, religion is like a rhinoceros: I don't have one, and I'd really prefer not to be trampled by yours.\n\n- Silas\n|\nlet's forget the hope, it's the secondary thing to motivate.the primary one is to approach for it.\n\n- kurbhatt\n|\nStrength is Life, Weakness is Death.Expansion is Life, Contraction is Death.Love is Life, Hatred is Death.\n\n- Swami\n|\nTake advantage of it now, while you are young, and suffer all you can, because these things don't last your whole life.\n\n- Gabriel García Márquez, Love in the Time of Cholera\n|\n[She wasn't] a logically reasoning woman, but God is good,