e hotter than Hell.\n\n- Steven\n|\nMy whole marriage to her, I finally realized, was a placeholder, leading me to this very day.\n\n- Barbara Avon, My Love is Deep\n|\nIf we try to measure Now, we find it's always gone, has become part of the past.\n\n- Aidan Chambers, The Toll Bridge\n|\nIt does not matter the evil you have experienced in your life, it is not God’s plan for you to be unhappy\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThings die. But they don't always stay dead. Believe me, I know.\n\n- Richelle Mead, Frostbite\n|\nI am awesome! I accept my amazing, awesome self exactly as I am in this moment. I love myself.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nA lot we have in our head,But things of heart are not yet dead,They have done none, but just fled,Out of us, Forgotten, just been bled..\n\n- Numey\n|\nThe reason people find it so hard to be happy is that they always see the past better than it was, the present worse than it is, and the future less resolved than it will be.\n\n- Marcel\n|\nWe may pick and choose to graft different fruits onto our spiritual tree, but regardless of what we call it, others will see a confusing fruit salad.\n\n- Matt Kellum, A Mirror Image: Looking Deeper Within to Reflect Jesus\n|\nWithin this new work of art a creature from beyond the reach of Humanity has insinuated herself and now lurks there at the heart of the mystery, a power unimagined before our time.\n\n- Villiers de L'Isle-Adam, Tomorrow's Eve\n|\nGive me the liberty to know, to utter, and to argue freely according to conscience, above all liberties.\n\n- John Milton, Areopagitica\n|\nAnd they danced with laughter and tears. They swung each other round and round, the first and last time in years.\n\n- Hubert\n|\nThe life of my people is to remember forever; each head granary is full. The life of your people is to forget: your thing granaries ('museums'), and not yourselves, are full.\n\n- Alice Walker, The Temple of My Familiar\n